The paper discusses privacy-preserving data publication, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a refined form of differential privacy, which is a machine learning technique, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses aggregate queries, which are a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
